ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[This is unusual as it is some years since a case of anthrax has been
reported in Montana, as well as early in the 'anthrax season'. The rain may
wash out an old grave. What is more common is that the spores will float to
the surface from a buried carcass as the ground fills with water. Unless
the cowboys skinned and butchered the dead cattle and got infected blood
into a cut or insect bite, or rubbed their faces and/or eyes while working,
human cutaneous cases are most unlikely. Enteric anthrax is rare in North
America. It is very wise to vaccinate the herd immediately on suspecting
anthrax. Any animal under antibiotic treatment, e.g., a dairy cow with
mastitis, must be revaccinated a week or ten days after the treatment has
ceased as the Sterne vaccine is live and is killed promptly by antibiotics
leaving the animal susceptible. - MHJ]
